\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 First of all can you tell me your name and present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Doris Nevill Tarling, 57 Wellington Road, Bushill Park, Enfield.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And you're a widow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What year were you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8737982 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 ?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 1924.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And the year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 1903.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 56 Brighton Road, Stoke Newington.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How many years did you live in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I should say - about eighteen months I think there - it could have been longer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you remember where you moved to after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, we went to Alexandra Grove, Finsbury Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And how long did you stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Nearly three years in there - then we went to 29 Woodbury Grove, Finsbury Park and then we moved out to North Finchley - no, not North Finchley - Woodbury Grove where did we go them - we went to Palmers Green.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I shou
ld say I was between eight and nine and when I was eleven we moved from Palmers Green to Sydenham and when I was fourteen we moved from Sydenham to North Finchley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So that would bring you to about the end of 1918 would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Er - well 1917 we moved to North Finchley and we stopped there until I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8737982 Married}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047  - that would be seven years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you remember why the family made these moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 My father liked moving - that's all - he enjoyed the moving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No other reason at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No reason at all - because he wasn't at home - it didn't matter where he was you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You were the only child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You didn't have any brothers or sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were any born that didn't live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Twenty-nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Er - I'm not sure where he was born but - the family were round Bells Pond Road part and he was educated at a school that I believe is still there at Clissold Park College. It is still there is it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, it was for the sons of gentleman you know. That's where he was educated at.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And what was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 He went into insurance. He became an agency manager with the British Widows assurance which has been gobbled up 
by the Prudential a few years back. Agency manager - that meant he travelled all over Great Britain, Wales and Scotland - hiring and firing and - people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 From the local offices?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. And he appeared in - in the law courts for cased at the various offices and that sort of thing - taking ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was that his only job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 He didn't have any others before of after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did he ever do any other part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And he continued in that until he retired?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Yes. He retired extra young because the Prudential bought the firm up you see and retired the old tops of the department - they were retired because they'd got their own people but I should say he - he retired before he was sixty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did he do anything after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Can you remember him ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 He had that one job all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Twenty-four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I don't know where she was born but I think it was near Hackney. I don't know the actual place.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But London anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did she have any jobs before she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8737982 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes. Yes. She - she was a boot buyer at a firm at Peckham who's name I
've forgotten and - before she went - my grandfather had a shop in Hoxton where he made heavy boots and shoes so that I mean they were all Londoners definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 It was in the family - the boot business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes. And mother - he didn't have moth
er there - he had - his next daughter helped him - cashier there - but she went into a shop - as a buyer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was that the only job your mother had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did she work after she got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8737982 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Never at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You can't remember her ever doing any other job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no. You didn't in those days - it was considered very bad to work when you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8737982 Married
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 . It meant that your - your husband couldn't keep you and it's not correct - oh you'd rather starve than work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Which house did you live in longest that you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, I can remember the highlights in a school in Green Lane - that was when I was five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How long were you in that house for in Green Lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, you see, I went there from Alexandra 
Grove and from Woodbury Grove I went to the Green Lane school so I was there for I suppose the first perhaps three years at that school - was a little day school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But which actual house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Sydenham would be the one I remember best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How many rooms were there in the house? How many reception rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Oh - a very large dining room - extremely large - extremely large lounge, a big kitchen and a big scullery, four bedrooms on the first floor and two on the top so it runs in the family. That was
 a lovely house and I can tell you how much that cost freehold - three hundred and eighty-five pounds. And it was a beautiful house - huge rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did just you and your mother and father live in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You didn't have any lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No other relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Always when she was younger - when she got older we couldn't afford it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you have anybody living in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Er - once or twice we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 While you were at this house in Sydenham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, we did. We had a French girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Can you remember what her duties were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, she used generally to help and she'd do a bit of cooking and she was more or less like a friend of the family 
but she would share the actual work with mother. She quite worked you know - quite - well as you would yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did she look after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Not in particular. I was a school and mother more or less looked after me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So her main task was to help with the housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you know if she had any set hours to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
No, she didn't - she didn't have that - she had a day off but no set hours - I mean if she wanted to go to bed she'd more or less go to bed sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 She wasn't a maid in the strict sense?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. Not in the strict sense - no she never dressed in maid's uniform or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How did you come to have a French girl - you didn't have an pair girls then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. Would be mother - they've always been mixed 
up with French people - they used to have French - girls come over and stop from France and I think he went to France - I don't know whether it came up like that or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How did you get on with this particular girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh I always got on all right.
 You see, being as only child you don't want anything from anybody - I was quite content to read all my - all my time away. And I reckoned to do five hours homework every night because I loved doing home - work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You were a self contained child really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What did you call this girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Annie. Annie - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What did your mother call her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 We all called her Annie - so did dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And what did she call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I think she always said Madame.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 To you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, she used to call me Doris. Mother was Madame.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Which is French for Mrs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes that's - yes, that's right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, we had a woman used to collect that in a basket - bring it back on - the next week. Mother used to usually wash mine - little things.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 This woman did it privately - it wasn't a laundry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Privately. Yes. Oh no, no. No, you used to get a lot of washerwomen in those days you know - they used drag a big basket - I've got one - and they'd bring it hom
e in the big wash - all beautifully laundered and then you'd go through - read it through while they was there and tip - of course it was a bit cheaper than now and we nearly always found women like that - wherever you moved - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your mother make your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 All of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Not I don't think my overcoats but most of my other things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did she make clothes for your father as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No shirts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no, dad bought those. She used to make most of hers and most of mine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were your clothes generally new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 They were new when I was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And where were they bought - the ones that your mother didn't make?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Now my liberty bodices were used to have, you know, I suppose she would go 
- tell you a shop - a place she used to do a lot of shopping at - Jones Brothers of Holloway - it's still there. It's a big modern shop now - quite a lot of stuff there and of course you used to get no end of small private shops for underwear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And did you have new clothes at any particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, not particular time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 When you needed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about shoes or boots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh she was very particular on that because that was, of course, her line of country so we used to always have new, new shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Your father never made boots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
No. No he was - never - his father did - same as mother's father. Dad was the youngest of five and he was treated rather as the baby so he went to the school for sons - how he laughed over that. Oh he did laugh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your father ever help your mother with any of the jobs in the house when he was at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, mother wasn't too strong and he would always do the fires when he was at home and fill the coal buckets and - dry up. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about cleaning or cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No he didn't do cleaning or cooking - not when he was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No, he didn't do anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Repairs or improvements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 He would do - carpentry work - you know - take time 3/8
 matter of fact that was a wash-stand and he put that top on it. He was quite handy with tools and bits round the house. Little things but no big jobs - no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did he dress or undress you or bath you or read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. But 
he didn't read or dress or undress me or bath me but - he used to play cards. I can remember playing cards - I can never remember a time when I didn't play cards with him - just he and I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Um - no. We used to always go to - the three of us, you know, Sunday walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did he ever look after you while your mother went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No I either - mother and I either went together or when I got older she went in the afternoons and I would come back from 
school - get my own tea and then she would come in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you have any tasks that you had to carry out regularly at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. I was expected to - clean my shoes and keep tidy but I never had any real tasks. Mother thought I was - got a lot of work
 to do she'd always do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 If you had a lot of homework to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But you didn't have to dust or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you have to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes, always went to bed early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What time did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I suppose - when I was at school - I must have been in bed at seven. Then I think we got more homework we got a bit later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 When you were young did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Mother used to when I was young and until I was about
 - let me see - until I was about nine I always slept in their room. Although there was room for me - but - I always had a bed in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So you didn't all go to bed at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no, I never - I never remember them going to bed - I was always a sleept.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Your mother would take you up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What age did you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I suppose - must be - I don't think it was before I was about nine - not completely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you have a room to yourself when you were nine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh bathroom. Oh a bathroom we had - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 When I was young I suppose about every other day - and if I got dirty when - I got sort of hot you know then I'd go into a bath only
 otherwise you couldn't have one every day because of heating the water which was heated by a range. So - father used to have a cold bath every morning - of course I wasn't up to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well of course summer time you'd have a clean frock about every other day unless you got dirty. Winter time about once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about underwear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well underwear - mostly the vests were once a week I think knickers twice a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Well, when there was just mother and I, say when dad was away, we always had our meals in the kitchen. When dad came home we bothered and put it in the dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you have any special occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Oh Christmas was always the dining room - the big room - had enormous dining rooms in all the houses. I suppose we had all the meals there except for breakfast then over holiday times - that's when we were all together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 When your father was home from work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes. See he come home Friday we'd eat in the dining room but just mother and I we didn't bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 In the scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Not the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. Separate scullery you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What did she cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Gas stove.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 She didn't cook on the range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No, she never used to range for cooking - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 When did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 About eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And who had breakfast?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Mother and me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 At the weekends when your father was home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Weekend - well, dad would be down too - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What did you usually eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, I had milk and they had tea - always tea never coffee and dad would have bacon. I would have it i
f I fancied it or else we used to have - I suppose we had toast or an egg - there weren't so many cereals then. Well, when cereals came on we went onto cereals and we had porridge when dad was home because he liked porridge. But as I say when he was away 
we just sort of took it easy mother and I alone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You had toast or ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. She usually cooked me an egg or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you have anything different on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No, not particularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about mid-day meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 We had a good mid-day meal and a light supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was this during the week while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Well then - I had a meal at school - a very good meal too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But if you didn't have it at school you'd have a good meal at mid-day and a light supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 There it went the same because mother always did a very big lunch and a light supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What would you have for lunch at the weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Roast beef, roast lamb and she used to be very good
 on puddings - raisin roll and rice puddings - she was mad on milk puddings you know and sometimes we'd have pastry and then jellies and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And what about the supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, then I think quite often I used to have bread and milk - I liked bread and milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Is this a bowl of milk with bread dropped in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
That's it. Yes. I was very fond of that. And I often used to have that - then of course she thought it wasn't enough you'd beat an egg up in it it makes it very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 This was usually at weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Well if you'd had a big meal ....
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about special occasions - did you eat anything special then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. Sometimes we used to have fish but not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 That wasn't a special occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no. 
It was just - when she felt like doing fish or it looked nice in the shop or something. See, you didn't get the packaged frozen fish or anything so you had to look at it on the - yes, if it looked very nice - she particularly liked skate which she did ver
y well and it was easy to see the bones you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did she bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did she make jam or chutneys and pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Oh yes, she made jam and - she did do chutney but not such a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did she bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Not vegetables - some fruit but ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And what about wine or medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 She made a very fine orange wine. But that was done just real oranges - none of the modern put this that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15663601\charrsid5596047  and the other in it - it was fe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 rmented you know sat in the b
in - I think it was for ten days and it used to blow the top off. It was very good that. Well, it turned into a liqu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15663601\charrsid5596047 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
r eventually because she bottle it and kept it - it was really very strong. And she used to make very fine jams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about medicines - did she ever make any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No, only sort of you know the old - vinegar and sugar and cough mixture and lemon and honey - nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your parents ever brew beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your parents grow their own vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Dad grew quite a lot of vegetables at one time but then he found that bending made his nose bleed so he gave it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did they buy many?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, used to buy all we had but, I don't remember that we had such an awful lot - I mean we had a small - we 
weren't very large eaters - you know a small cabbage would do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Would you buy tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh what then? Oh no, no, it was all fresh. They weren't thought of dried - tins very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Could you buy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I don't know - I don't think you could buy dried - you could get the old green peas - and you used to have split }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15663601\charrsid5596047 peas - mother used to make peas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
 pudding and haricot beans but I don't think there was much of the other and of course the tinned stuff until I think Heinz
 started their baby foods - tinned stuff - very suspect in those days, very, very suspect. It was when Heinz bought their stuff in people began to think it was pure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So you had fresh vegetables?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Pretty well all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your parents keep any livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No hens or pigs or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Ever tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. Always fresh - mother would make a stew you see for one day and it would las
t for the next like that with a fresh root crop and things during the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did she ever get any extra meat from poaching or did she always buy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no, she always bought it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you remember ever seeing your mother having less food than you so that you or your father could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No, I think we had ample in those days. It wasn't until they got onto rationing they had to be careful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 That was the second world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your father have more meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Yes, he used to eat - have a bigger appetite than we but it wasn't - I don't think it was because mother couldn't afford it I think it was considered a man's portion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes, yes. Yes, I was allowed to talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Could you choose what you wanted to eat or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
I was supposed to eat a bit of everything. In moderation they weren't - they weren't sort of bigoted about food but it was good for me I was expected to eat it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What would happen if you left a little bit uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, I think they'd feel something was wrong with it which would have upset me and I should have felt I'd got to eat it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So you generally ate what was put on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I generally ate it - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Or did you help yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
No, but I was allowed to say that's enough so, so you know mother would say will you have a little more and I'd day no thank you and that was all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 If you wanted anything passed like the salt could you just ask for it or would you have to wait until it was offered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. I could ask for it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
I was expected to hold my knife and fork in a certain way and not to lounge at table but not - bolt upright - I could sit comfortably as the Bible says.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And when could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Well, if I'd finished and they were almost finished I could ask and usually they would let me go down but if you had visitors you were not expected to get down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And did you always have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How was the meal served - who served the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Father first then me and then mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 When you had your French girl or anybody else living in where did they eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
She didn't eat with us - now - she ate in the - in the - I imagine we must have eaten in the dining room then - and she ate in the kitchen which would bring us into maid - maid status wouldn
't it - yes. I'm sure she - she didn't eat with us. I think when we - if we just had a cup of tea and a biscuit and she bought it in and mother and I - you know - when I come home from school - she would have a cup of tea then like - she'd sit here - not 
at the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 When your father was away did she still eat separately from you and your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you know if she had different food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I don't think she did. I think she had exactly what we did. I know mother didn't get anything - 
whether she wanted anything different I couldn't say but to the best of my knowledge it was all cooked and done the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was she the only living-in person that you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, I wouldn't say she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
No. No, because she was always told an only child was spoilt therefore she was not going to spoil me and she was harder on me than - than she need have been in a way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 She went a little too far the other way you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 That's right. She did it quite deliberately because she said she wasn't going to have me spoilt - spoken of as a spoilt child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 If you had any worries could you share them with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No. Neither of my parents would I tell any worries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was your father affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 More so than your mother would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, you see, not being there during the week it might have seemed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You had him just for weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. That you - naturally he
 would come in and sort of make a fuss of you and that sort of thing but he wasn't - wasn't there all the week that you obviously would make more fuss having come home after being away for five days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You were alone with your mother quite a lot weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How did you get on with her - could you chatter to here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh we just used to talk ordinary - but we were both quiet people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How did they expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, to be generally obedient a
nd - more or less do as I was told, I could register a protest but it might not get through - but they were very good in so far as - my schooling and hobbies and things like that. They were very good and would always help me in any way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 They were interested in what you were doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did they ever give you any example of how to get on with other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 If you were playing with other children and one of the children hit you would your parents ever suggest how y
ou should treat the child in return?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Oh no, but they wouldn't have allowed me to hit her back. Oh no. I knew that yes, and I was expected when we had guests to let them have anything they wanted of mine because it was polite. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What kind of person do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Mother wanted me to be a school teacher. Father didn't mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did they make you feel that certain things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no, except that you'd just got to sort of live an ordinary - godly and sober life you might say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 A career was quite important to your mother though?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. She - she very much - I think it was because she would have liked to have been a teacher herself. I found out after of course that
 my head - headmistress wanted me to be a teacher too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What did your parents think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Well, it was - you weren't supposed to swear unless it was really something awful you know - I mean you dropped the hammer on your toe then father wo
uld say damn - even mother would then but you were not supposed to like you hear so many people - bloody this and bloody that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were you allowed to swear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, I didn't ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 If you'd dropped a hammer on your toe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, I'd ha
ve been allowed to say damn because it was considered, you know, that that sort of letting your feelings go sort of business but I was not expected to swear generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, if it was a so
rt of conversation they thought I knew anything about they wouldn't mind but normally they wouldn't expect me to say anything 'cos they wouldn't have thought it was worth listening to. But if it was about school or anything I was doing then I could say.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 If they had visitors you wouldn't be expected to chip in with your point of view.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh no, no, not unless - yes that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 If you did something they disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well very occasionally mother slapped my hand. And - I might be sent out of the room if she was really very angry. But nothing more.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was it only your mother or did your father ever punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Father - father didn't punish me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Is this because he wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I don't think so - I think I was a very biddable infant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How often do you think you were punished in those small ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Shouldn't think more than about once a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Can you remember any specific incident when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. And that - I still feel it'
s unjust now. It was mother's younger sister we were talking - I think it was about Cinderella - and I turned to her and said quite innocently because as I told you I'm a big reader I said oh don't you know about Cinderella - and she said no. And my mothe
r went for me no end - she said that I was trying to be superior and I shouldn't talk like that to her - and then she got angry with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 This was your mother's sister who was younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Yes. I was quite horrified that she hadn't heard
 of it. Oh I did get into trouble - I got sent up to bed. For being superior - thinking myself superior. I feel it was unjust - I do - I couldn't have been more than eight either and I can see the room now - it was in Sydenham - see mother standing there 
going for me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Would you say that you received your ideas about how to behave from - more from one parent than the other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, I think they both sort of - did their part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. Not in a way - you see, my birthday comes in August so we were usually on holiday so I missed everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you receive any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Er - well they used to give me some little thing but the main present of course would be when we got home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 After the holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. So we used to have a big Christmas party to make up for you couldn't have one on your birthday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You didn't have a birthday party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you have anything special to eat on your birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 It was treated like any other days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. We might have an extra donkey ride but nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Can you remember anything you did with your mother and father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, we used to have lovely Christmases when I was
 young. We used to go and visit my grandmother who lived in Eleanor Road, Hackney and - we'd get on the tram car - Finchley or Palmers Green or wherever we happened to be living - we'd go all the way down to Hackney and grandma would have gathered all the
 
people round who were stopping Christmas night you see and then the - I suppose she'd have about twenty people there and - room wasn't as large as this but she'd drawn all the tables together all the forms all the way round the table and half the aunts an
d
 uncles would be stopping - mother being the oldest the sister would give the bedroom up to her - and the others would all be dotted about - some even slept on the dining room table I expect sometime. And then - Auntie Florrie would do most of the cooking
 
- mother would help. Grandma didn't do anything - she just saw that the girls got on with it wouldn't let - great big cooking - range goin you know - great big stirrer with a great big gas stove and everybody rushing about. That's how I tell you that moth
e
r was rather hard - various uncles - we had various relatives used to be round about - used to pop in you know on Christmas morning and the doors - give the youngsters - my aunt a year younger my uncle a year older than me so there were three - oh here's 
a
 shilling to buy yourself something. Mother wouldn't allow me to accept money. The other's did. And one uncle said - never mind girl stick it up your bloomer leg she won't know. I did. That was her uncle - my grandmother's brother actually. But see, and t
he others were all allowed to have a drink - you know - children always had port in those days, just a little drop - I wasn't allowed to. No, no. I've had to make up for it since. It wasn't meant unkindly it was just to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 This was their idea of how children should behave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Yes, it was - yes, yes. And then we'd have - we'd stop there - wed have an enormous meal - the postman always came in for a Christmas dinner and sat in the corner and then auntie'd bring in the pudding you know, all lit up sort o
f thing then in the afternoon they'd do washing up - we children used to play. And there'd be a cup of tea and cake - then they'd - the drawing room was upstairs - and they'd all gather round - oh there'd be hundreds of them - the piano we'd all sing and 
dance and well I say dance - you couldn't dance much but you know - have a very merry time they were all - all relatives of the family.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And you enjoyed that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Thoroughly enjoyed it. Down - gran was - as I say there were nine children of hers and 
they'd come with their various husbands and wives so to speak.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Your mother was one of nine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Yes. She was the eldest of nine. And down the road was grandma's sister with her family of about eight and they'd all be backwards and forwards you see s
o that - it was a real old fashioned family Christmas - nowadays of course they say well what did you do? You didn't really do anything. You know we all did a bit of a sing - we could all play the piano and - they'd all get merry - they were - even if the
y really - they wouldn't be considered voices now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Would you play games and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No, see, there were too many of us. But we'd all join in the singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you have a piano at your own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, always - always had a piano all my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And you could play and your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Dad couldn't play from music - he'd vamp any tune you like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you all sing - I mean you and your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Mother and I did - dad would 
join in a chorus but he never sang as a - oh I had to sing as a child - Christmas time I had to sing. We all sang - we all played.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you ever sing together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, not when I was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Or make music as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. Carol singing - yes we all joined in - in general carol singing but not as not as you say as family music.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your parents ever play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. And dad was very good he would make me a - I remember he made me a large tent and all differ
ent things and they - mother dressed Teddy as a boy scout - this sort of thing and they - when we were home I would put perhaps a show on up in the attic with bits and do a little entertainment on my own for them and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Always. Always - yes - books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Some of these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Some of them are from my home - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, not - I don't remember mother having a magazine. Mind you they weren't so prevalent then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Always. Oh yes, always newspapers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 A daily newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did they ever read aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No, we all read our own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Before you could read did they read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
No, I don't remember mother - them reading to me. I expect mother helped me when I was learning to read in fact I'm sure she did but she didn't actually read a story to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Can you remember a funeral at all in the family when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
I can't think whose it was - 1918 - don't think I can remember one in the family. I can remember King Edward VII and I didn't know I'd remembered it I'm - because in my mind I could 
see his horse - you know he had a horse in front of his funeral. I remember a black coat for his funeral and I sat on the paving some-where in Hyde Park and - I could remember a dog and I've never said anything and I thought I imagined it until I saw it o
n
 the films a few years back and the dog was there so I must have seen it. Yes. Yes. I can't remember a - a family funeral - I've an idea they were kept very quiet in those days. You know, if anybody died you kept it from the children sort of thing, as the
y would say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were you taken out visiting neighbours and friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Quite a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 With whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Ever with both your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Occasionally but you see dad being away when he came home he preferred to stop at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were you ever taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes, yes, of course, went shopping. And matinees and visiting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you go shopping for food with her as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Not just for clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. Food as well.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Yes, but not until I was about - twelvish 'cos then he and I used to go cycling and we - we'd stop - nowhere special but if we saw anything we'd stop and perhaps look over a house or if there was litt
le sale we'd go and see a sale and that sort of thing. Then we went on country holidays we'd take our bikes and cycle round then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Your mother didn't cycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, she didn't cycle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you remember any other outings with your parents, for example on bank holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I only remember the one to Hendon to the air - that was both parents - I forget when they had that air display.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 That was a special outing to an air display?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15663601\charrsid5596047 When you went up in the airplane}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 That's right - yes. The biplanes - the biplanes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You can't remember when that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Can't remember - no, I - when do they normally have those displays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How old were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Now let me - Hendon - I suppose it would be about 1914 - 15 I should think -
 no the war was on then - just before the war I should think - I don't think we had an air display with the war did we - no - can't remember - I remember going up of course and I can remember seeing the - those German thing coming down that was in the fir
st world war - zeppelin - heard of that coming down in flames - we looked out of our bedroom window and saw it coming down. It looked wired.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You went on regular outings though didn't you with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, I mean holiday times we would go - 
mother would always take me to a matinee in town and usually one day to the shops and that sort of thing and we'd go to the pictures and dad would sometimes come with us to the pictures on a Saturday. Oh yes we went out quite a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 When you went away on your summer holidays how long did you go for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Fortnight as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And did you go every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 All three of you together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Where did you generally go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, for several years we went to Leigh-on-sea that's near Southend and then for several more years we went to Bournemouth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What did you do when you were on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh we just walked round and paddled you know - father could swim - I used to go in but couldn't swim - mother didn't swim. Occasiona
lly she paddled if it was very hot.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was this in a long dress like you showed me in the pictures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Yes, yes. And - donkey rides - oh I always had donkey rides - cost a whole six-pence, that was terrible. Yes, but you see Bournemouth is uphill - h
ome where we went mother used to get a very nice little apartment you see and do the - they do the - she'd do the catering and they'd cook it. Up the top of the hill there - that was when we were - before they got more money - when we went to a boarding h
ouse after that. But we always went to those two places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You enjoyed your holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Can you tell me how you spent Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, I should say that my days were fairly uneventful but dad was home on Saturdays so if he was doing t
he garden I should be pottering about with him. And then probably in the afternoon we'd go for a little walk - we usually had a dog and very occasionally we'd go to the pictures in the evening and then I suppose I should go to bed. Always had to do some p
ractice on the piano every day - half an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I used to go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 In the morning or afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Afternoon. But dad usually pottered round the house and mother did the work. And I finished my homework. I n
early always went to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you have different clothes on Saturdays and Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 On Sundays when we went out - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You had your special Sunday clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, that's right - Sunday outfit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you play game on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes, I was allowed to play any games if there were any to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your parents think it was wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no, they didn't - no, no, they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your parents attend a place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you know what denominations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Church of England. I was christened and that sort of thing but ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So just you went to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, just me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, I never went on any outings. There were
 some but you had to be very poor to be - to go on an outing then. You see, we were middle class might be lower middle class, but it wasn't quite the thing to go on an outing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were there any other soc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15663601\charrsid5596047 ial activities that were organiz}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 ed by the church? That you did take part in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Er - Band of Hope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Well, that was when you - you promised to become teetotal and you had a little meeting - Bible reading - I don't think it goes now if you don't know - and of course there was the
 Primrose League - that was where you signed that you would never drink for the rest of your life. They were all church activities. I haven't heard of any of those lately.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did they have little meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. At Sunday school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 This was part of the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well you joined in if you want to and have a little extra half hour in the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And you chose to join this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well I chose - I think I only went a few times but - I did join it. I always got on alright with e
verybody although I didn't - I didn't need to go on outings - there was plenty to do at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you belong to a choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. I did at school in - when we went to Finchley - they put me in the choir there but not in church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I was going to ask you if the church ran any temperance clubs but presumably this Band of Hope was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, that's - that's - yes - Primrose League definitely was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 They were two different things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Why were they different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I expect - I expect they just weren't joined together don't you. I don't know why they were different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 It wasn't one for young people and one for elderly people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh no, no, no - you could be any age to join the Primrose League.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What did you do in the Primrose League for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I don't know that we did anything except talk - the horrors of drinking and sign the pledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Always said prayers at night - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Er - a little. He was a Conservative - very Conservative all his life.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Why do you think he held those views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, the same re
ason as I hold them. That is to way I think Conservatives have a better knowledge of - of foreign affairs and things connected with dividends and money - not that I think they've got better brains but this - its more or less traditionally through the fami
l
ies and it's like so many things, if you've always been used to that thing and brought up with that thing you're better at it than somebody who's just come in fresh. That is .... well, yes - he thought it - and if you speak to people who - who's - well, w
hose money depends on dividends and things like that they're nearly always Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about your mother - did she have any interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 She followed my dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 She didn't have any real interest herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you remember them voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh they always voted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Every time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Yes, mother used to get on to the count too always - would be interested in that form - in that sense - always - year after year he'd do - you know, do the counting for the election.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And they both voted Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
In some places at that time it was felt that men risked losing their employment if they voted differently from their employers - were you ever aware of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. And 
probably you see in - dad being in insurance business they wouldn't be inclined to know how they voted would they - it's not like a big factory or the works where they sort of - one can tell the other - when you get the ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You were not aware of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
No, I never heard anybody losing their job because of that. In fact I think it was freer then than it is now. Because I think - I don't think people really - well you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15663601\charrsid5596047 
just voted - they weren't so - im}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 mersed in politics - a lot of youngsters are ter
ribly immersed in politics I've noticed. And I don't think they know anything about it because - they can only know what they've read and in any subject you can read one side which is all right - you can read the other side and that's just as all right - 
it isn't until you've had a few years to see it working that you can - take any definite line.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Draw conclusions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. You must have something to put them together. Half of them I think vote differently because their parents voted they other way y
ou know, just the opposite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 For spite?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was your father or mother active members of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you remember his working for the Conservative party at an election?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, never apart from the counting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did they take part in any political activity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 When your parents were not working how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well dad would read and mother would sew or read, she was great at sewing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Your father liked gardening as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Or just as a necessity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, he quite liked it until it got too much for him and he liked to potter and do little things as I say a bit of carpentry }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15663601\charrsid5596047 or}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047  if mother said, well the curtain's fallen down, well he'd put it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
I don't think so - I think she mainly visited. When - when I was older - because she a big - a member of a big family - she would go round to see them - that was her way of keeping up with them - they
 were very - well they still are actually - they keep up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Her brothers and sisters you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Her - her family - people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You mean did she go to a social club - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 If she went to the cinema she went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 She would take me - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 When did your father get home from work in the evening on a Friday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Mostly - in time for dinner - meal. Yes. Occasionally he wouldn't be but then he would let us know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did he attend any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Well, he was a Free Mason for many years - I think he got quite high in that - and he used to play bowls - this is when he was a young man - and he played billiards extremely well. I couldn't tell you where but I know there was a club f
or it - so it must have.... Mother would go to the Freemasons dinner when they had them ladies night and that sort of thing but apart from that she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did she ever go with him to play bowls or watch him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your father take part in any sport apart from the bowls - like racing or cricket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, he used to go sailing - in the holidays with friends. Holidays with his men friends occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did he attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 He had but he was very much against betting because o
ne of his very dear friends had become - bankrupt owing to some betting business - they'd gone into a bookies business in some way and he'd been betting and got in an awful mess and father said well, I - I'll come into your business for a year and show yo
u what - which way you should never bet. And he went into this friends business - betting business at the bookies - really temporarily of course as a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15290813\charrsid5596047 \{ILLEGIBLE\}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047  - and he put it all straight but - and proved to him that the bookmaker always won - there was 
no point in you betting. And he would never bet. He would have a - well a ticket on the Derby that's - just the once but never regular betting because he said bookmakers always win.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your parents belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No sick club or funeral club - anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No. Dad was in insurance but he never insured himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Mostly my class mates - and we would go there to tea - they would come to tea with me. I never remember picking anybody up off hand.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you ever play with any of the neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I did at Sydenham - yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Other children along the road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, the neighbours. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Next door neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 We were very friendly with them. But I didn't know anybody else along the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Either in their homes or in mine or in the garden. Never in the street - you weren't allowed in the streets when I was a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But in your garden you were allowed to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh - we had tea parties and imitation cooking where you mixed custard powders and things like that - we didn't actually cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Why was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I think mother thought it made her stove dirty and 
- my own children had their own little spirit stoves and they cooked - they boys - but we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 The boys cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes, when they was young - oh they did a lot - had to eat all their pancakes made with turpentine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But you never got round to the actual cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What other games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Of course we had hoops and - I think we also had a wig-wam in the garden and a teddy bear dressed as a soldier or something like that. Never dolls - I didn't like dolls although I liked my dolls house with its furniture and - very nice that was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you play with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 It wasn't just to look at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no, I played with that a lot - rearranged it you know - swept the carpets and this sort of thing. That 
was very interesting but - I did have a baby doll but as far as I can remember it was mostly laid on the bed and I very rarely played with it although it undressed and dressed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you play any indoor games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 We could play most games if we had to
. We had ludo and snakes and ladders and - snap and beat-your-neighbours-out-of-doors - all the old games. We've always had a lot of games - that type of game in the house - all quiet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, I imagine I would have been allowed but I never wanted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Your mother wouldn't have been cross?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I'm sure she wouldn't - she'd have just yanked me off and put me in something clean and washed my hands that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Well, there I should say I was very carefully shepherded never to meet anybody that would displease my parents because I don't ever remember being stopped from going with anybody. As I say she fetched me from school and she took me to s
chool and I should say that she did it in a very nice way but those that she thought weren't quite the thing would be carefully shepherded in the other direction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Can you remember ever being invited to tea anywhere where your mother wouldn't let you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, as far as I know I always went where I was asked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. I don't even remember any youth organisations - oh well there would have been the - what the - the Crusaders and that - but I wasn't.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 When you were at school did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
No. I always liked studying and I thoroughly enjoyed studying and - when I wasn't studying I was reading or making lists of books I'd like to read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You didn't collect things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, not un
til - I was fourteen - fifteen - and then the school had - it was sort of competition in our form for collecting wild flowers and we'd go all over the countryside pressing and collecting wild flowers and I won the prize for that - I've still got the colle
ction too. All - they all had to be named with where they were found when they were found and their Latin names. Wherever I went I pressed and collected these flowers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But this was for school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 That was for school - oh no, no, it was for school - 
several of us who were very interested and we used to go round cycling week ends - girls - and find specimens so forth and then I used - always used to act at school - was always in the school play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you enjoy that then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were you good at it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I was always in them so I suppose I must have been quite good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Always had a dog at home but it wasn't definitely my dog - it was the family dog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you look after it at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh, I liked - I'd take it out for a walk. I don't remember brushing it - I may even have done that - but mother always fed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Oh, tepidly you know if I felt like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You didn't have your own little plot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No, no, but I was encouraged to go round and find out the names of flowers and that - if we didn't know them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. Don't ever - that would have been too quiet for me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You went out for walks though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Oh yes. M
ind you you always had a Sunday walk when I was very young, in your best clothes and after Sunday school you went for a walk - mother and father and if you were very good we'd call in and buy a quarter of pound of sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 On a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Four ounces for tuppence then. They were best ones. You could get four onces for a penny - they were not quite so good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But what about real walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, well we were mainly town you see, we didn't - it was only just sort of round the park you would go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you ever go with your friends for a walk round the park?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, just with my parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You used to go bicycling a lot didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 With your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was this a hobby or a particular pleasure of yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, I think it grew out of the fact it was a way of getting round the places where we shouldn\rquote 
t have got, you see we didn't have motor car or anything like that and it was better you could get out of the way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you go to special places to look at something or did you just ride round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
No, we used just to cycle round the - the lanes and sort of follow the next one and the next one. And of course I always cycled to school you see. So that it was quite - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you ever go cycling with your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Oh yes, when I got fourteen we used to go out quite a bit in holiday times - at South Mimms woods and round there - still looking for flowers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh, at school we always played - now let me see
 - hockey, netball, tennis, fives - which is a game you play against a wall with balls and badminton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you do any of these out of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Badminton I did out of school as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was this a club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, and tennis - I belonged to a tennis club - that would be when I was about fourteen - fifteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was this just for youngsters - could this have been a youth organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No, it was run privately by the club was run by somebody in the next road we were all more or less the sa
me sort of people - we were all under twenty-one but it wasn't a youth club it was just one friend to another would gradually join up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And all you did was play badminton or tennis?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And tennis - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You didn't have any other activities with the group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you go to any theatres and concerts or music-halls or cinemas while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Not only that, we had outings from the school to theatres too. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You went to all of those did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Mm. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Which did you go to most? You told me before you often went to a matinee with your mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Yes, that was the cinema. I also went to the theatre - I should say it was about equal, theatres and cinemas. And concerts not so much - music-hall not quite so many because that - we usually went when father was home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But with your mother you'd go to the cinema and theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 We used to - yes, yes, we used to - that was in holiday times you see when dad wasn't there we used to go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Penny a week. Every week - and then when I began to get older I said dad you know this ought to go up I'm getting older - so we had a little agreement whereby he gave me 
a penny for the next year and another penny the following year until we got up to sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How old were you when you were getting your sixpence?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh, I must have been quite eleven or twelve by the time I was getting sixpence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What did you spend the money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I only just saved it to buy Christmas presents for other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Because your parents bought you sweets anyway on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So you didn't have to ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, and I had to have something to buy - some presents with - mostly did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Can you remember ever buying other things with your pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Books. Yes, I'd save up until I had enough money and then I would go to - and look round Mud}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15290813\charrsid5596047 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 ies - the big book shop - and buy a book that I'd - got a long, long list of books I wanted - and I'd buy one or two of those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did anyone - was it only Annie who helped your mother with the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, she was the only one that lived in. Before that we had - we used to have somebody that came about twice a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 A daily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Daily - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Part time helper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Yes. A char lady we used to call them. Char lady. Mother thought that sounded better than char-woman you see, so they were char-ladies. Yes. It was quite right. And then of course the washer-woman who would come and take the washing away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did any of your mother's family ever help with anything in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You mean in their house? Not in our house - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 They never came to lend your mother a hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no, mother was the oldest and was expected to help them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 The younger ones weren't expected to help the older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, and the - and the brothers were never expected to do a thing - they were waited on hand and foot by the girls. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 If your mother was ill, you said that she wasn't always in very good health, and was confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I don't think she was ever confined completely to bed. It was mainly this bad back she suffered from.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 If ever that were really bad so she couldn't do some of the housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, she'd leave it unless she could get a woman in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But the family didn't help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, the family wouldn't come round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Nor neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. The only one that ever helped at all when - and
 I can remember - I say very ill, must have been once at Sydenham - the next door neighbour there was a banker's wife and very good and I have an idea she came in and gave mother breakfast once. But nobody that - that's all - no - looking after me and ...
.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And no regular help or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your parents have their relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. Not really - when they were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8737982 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How often did you see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I don't see father's relations very much because his fathe
r and mother had died - his father died before I was born - his mother died when I was six months old so to my knowledge I don't remember seeing her. We used to visit his brother quite a bit who lived in Folden Road, Stoke Newington, number ninety-two, an
d I can - that's how I know it. He had two girls and we would visit there I suppose roughly averaging once a month because it might be a bit more in the holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your father ever go on his own without you or your mother do you know? Do you think he saw them more regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
No. No, no, because he wasn't home you see. And mother's people - well the eldest brother we didn't visit because his wife was a bit odd and said she couldn't have a child seeing her house - nobody knew why. She couldn't ha
ve a child seen seeing her house - she said I used to look at it - this was when I was about eight I think. So we don't go - but the others - of course for some time they were still at grandmothers and I would visit them - we visited grandma I suppose we 
averaged once a month there - roughly yes - I say if we missed a month we'd probably go twice in the holidays or something like that but I should say that was about an average.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And you usually went to their house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did any of the family come to your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Only occasionally - but mostly you see we would all meet at grandmas so she would see us all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And you had your Christmas party there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. But dad had business friends - very good ones too - they would come and visit us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 His business friends would come the home would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes. And - mother had one or two friends left from when she was in business and they used to come and stop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So she had some friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And he had some friends of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And the friends that they had in common - can you remember?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, I think they were mostly sort of - grown together with them if you know - father'd intr
oduce mother and mother got friendly with the wife as father knew the husband and they would get to be mutual friends in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Would they visit each others houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Or would they tend to come to your parents home mainly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, we used to visit them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were friends often invited to your home - your parents friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, I don't suppose we ever saw anybody say more than about once a month - we were very quiet home really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Oh they'd come for a meal - always. Not necessarily drinks - I don't think we had very much drink in the house - probably we couldn't afford it. But always plenty to eat and mother would go to a lot of trouble to have things nice for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were drinks expensive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Well not com - not as they seem today - but if you were on a - I mean I think they said whisky was about four and six a bottle but then if you haven't got a lot - if you're running everything on about four or five pounds a w
eek then four and six a bottle still sounds a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your visitors come on any particular days or for special occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, just weekends you see when dad would be home. Unless it was one or two of mothers - old business friends who might pos
sibly come during the week when they'd usually stop 'til weekends to see dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 They'd stay overnight you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Would you say that on the whole friends that came to the house were your mother's or fathers or equally both of their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Mainly mother's I should say. Yes, mainly mother's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Never?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I never remember them calling in - I - only - as I say the only person who ever popped in was our Sydenham neig
hbour. And - there we were - whatever the - we call that at the most neighbourly friendly family we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And they would just pop in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your parents go together on their own without you to visit neighbours or friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh no, only very special occasions like a Masonic dinner or - or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 If they went out to visit friends you went too?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I went too - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements. What do you think you
r parents or what did they do when they were together with their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Sang. Father played. Mother sang. I was always expected to sing or recite. The others just the same. We all expected - were expected to - didn't matter whether you could sing o
r not - you still sang. As I say father could bang out accomplishments to anybody you see say - just say a verse and then he'd go off quite happy - couldn't read music. But he'd play anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So music took quite an important part in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
No, not - I don't remember playing any games. Not when I was very young - it was mostly you see you'd have - somebody would sing - somebody would play then perhaps you'd have a - a drink or a sandwich or some
thing or a glass of lemon squash and then somebody else would sing. Then you'd all have a chat about people you knew there was a lot of talking in those days. That would be the general pattern - yes. If there were more than one child they could go off and
 have a little game in - in the other room you see, yes, leaving the parents - the grown ups to get on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And it was mainly talking and music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Many people divide society into different social classes or groups - in that time before 1918 d
id you think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
I think without my actually thinking about it you sort of automatically knew - or were expected to know that - somebody was lower middle class or below that and of course when you got 
to the upper middle class they were - apt to consider them-selves very upper. I mean things were just not done - for no reason, you knew they were not done but ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How would you have divided society?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I should say there was what they would then say the lower classes which mainly consisted of labourers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You'd call them lower classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Yes. Then you'd get the lower middle class which I should say teetered between lower and middle middle and then you'd get the upper who were in a higher inc
ome bracket and probably always had a resident maid or two. And they definitely did consider you should - well - dry up or anything like that - you just sat - the tea was handed to you you know - and you never did anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And you just grew up knowing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You just sort of grew up - you were quite used to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You would have put your own family in the middle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I should say the middle because you see, dad was a professional. They went then largely by occupation. Whereas mother being in a 
shop wasn't really middle. She'd have been lower -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Lower middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 She'd be - we would be sort of middle middle because he was professional - we wouldn't be in the upper because of the income bracket.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What sort of people would belong to the same sort of class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Well, I should say - you'd get the people who were in sufficient income not to pay any insurances - I should say that's over three pounds a week - you would not - you didn't pay any national payments whatever it 
was. State insurance that was what that was. I should say you could take that as your marking line then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What sort of people were your parents friends - they would have been the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 All about the same - yes - mother's you see mainly had been buyers and - only know one was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8737982 
Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
 to one of the buyers at Whitecliffes - you know William Whitely and the sisters there - there were three sisters - the other two sisters had all were - they'd all been buyers or under manageresses obviously had worked 
them 3/8 selves up so they must have started at the bottom and they were all fairly well educated - they'd all been educated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 These were lower middle class people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Well, you see now mother's father had left school very, very young, was more
 or less keeping himself by the age of fourteen. He could read and write and was very intelligent - did very well, became a boot manufacturer. He built himself up - so he must have been intelligent - but mother and her sisters all went to school and were 
taught quite properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So you would say that her friends were generally lower middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Whereas dad being in the insurance tended to meet insurance people who were all professional class most of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What other people - what other jobs would you have said would be middle middle class? For example your neighbour who was a banker's wife?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
He would be - yes - he was - or he became bank manager so there again would be - he was sort of under - what do they call it assistant bank man
ager - I believe it is - he wasn't manager then. He left Sydenham and went to a big house at Dulwich as bank manager so he was just - must have been one below.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were they in the same social class as your ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, as my father - definitely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Can you think of any other types of person who would be in the same class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Er - well I supposed accountants would have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about the working classes and what sort of people - you said labourers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes - and - more or less you mi
ght find they went largely by education because most of the labouring classes and quite a number of the servants and that sort of thing had very little education. You see, at that time it was really quite considered wrong to be educated if you were lower 
-
 if you were lower class. You got that attitude from the lower classes - they were going above themselves if they got educated. And that's extended to quite an our time - I've got one personal experience of that - I've got one very good friend of mine now
 
- I've known her twenty years and her son - he was - he is a clever boy - he's now forty. Well, this lady had worked her way up - she's - she got what education she could but her mother - the father died - and mother and she carried on - she used to work 
f
or three and six a week - when she was a child - doing washing up after school so as to make ends meet. Well, when this son of hers got a scholarship from the - local school there to go into St Albans school which is a public school she and her sisters th
ought oh he couldn't possibly go there - he wasn't - coming from the right home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And this was the attitude when you were growing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Very much so. Mind you she did but the headmaster went for her. But it definitely grew because this boy became a 
great friend of my eldest boy and I remember my eldest boy said, "oh you must meet, Mrs Baker when she goes down the street - call out to her mother, "and she apparently was pathetically grateful because he went in and visited her son and she said you kno
w I never felt with him that he was looking at what I'd got."
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And this is left over from the 1918 days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Left over yes, yes, yes. It was all like that it was - you must not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So you place your social class mainly on educations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. And enough money to be able to appreciate or benefit by it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What sort of people would be the upper middle classes then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, they'd be the one I should say that had made enough money - their parents had made enough money for them to start where th
e parents left off. They didn't have to work hard for what they'd got - they could therefore go on and take advantage - the leisure advantages of - with time to spare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 They were the second generation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one class differently from people of another class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No, my father and mother didn't believe in that at all. You had to be polite to everybody. Irrespective of what they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were you ever told to curtsy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No. No, I was a good as anybody but I was not better than anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you have to show respect to any particular person or any particular type of person? Apart from the general respect to adults?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I don't think so, I was never taught to sort of - regar
d anybody as superlatively better. I mean I should 3/8 automatically regarded the Queen as - above every - thing - but that was quite automatic, we'd all do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Some people for example would curtsy or something similar to a minister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh no, I shouldn't have regarded a minister any more than I do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was there anyone you called Sir or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. Only the headmaster. But that was because it was school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these sort of ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I think mother liked a fair amount of respect and she liked her people to say Madam - sort of thing to her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Which people - the people who worked for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, I think she would have definitely expected respect from them then - very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about shop - people in shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
People in shops then always said Madam. Not luv like they do now. I mean if - if a - if a shop assistant didn't say "do you like this Madam," you'd say oh I won't go in that shop again - they don't know how to behave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So she would be shown respect automatically in that way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Certainly tradesmen and people who worked for her - she would expect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Expect - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Would your father expect this similarly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Er - I should say 
he would expect his men to think of him but I don't think he actually felt - he would automatically get it because he hired and fired all over the country. So they would naturally treat him as well as possible. Mmm. And of course as he was quite used to t
aking up law suits and then again you were treated with proper respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 In your district who were considered the most important people in the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I wouldn't remember. Not Stoke Newington.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about Finchley - that was your next move wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, Stoke Newington to Finsbury Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, anywhere can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
I can't think of anybody very important. Not that we considered important - I think that's what you mean - no, I don't remember - not anywhere actually. Sydenham, Finchley or anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Can you think of anybody that anyone else might have considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, I can't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 There was no local squire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh no. No, nobody like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about the shopkeepers - who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I imagine they all kept with themselves because you know they'd got a lot of trader's associations.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Can you tell me what sort of people the clergymen would have associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well they'd associate with church helpers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Er - they would call and - if they thought you had enough money - I feel rather bitter about this although I am a church goer and they're different now, but they did tend to keep with their parishoners who had things and who would produce sumptuous teas a
nd that sort of thing for them and who would give - sums to the sales of work and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You noticed this even as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Oh you could, if the Vicar came to tea everybody would rush round putting the best cloth on and getting t
he best china out and - and going round the corner and buying a nice cake because that was what he expected.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But he never came to tea with your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No. No, my people were not church goers - but I say I was and I was confirmed although my
 mother wasn't. But it was quite noticeable even then. And - it's a pity - it's given not only clergy, but the church workers, a very bad name. Because I know if I went round myself I would be asked - are you from the church? No. Oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So this was typical?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 It wasn't just in your street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
No, no, it was typical - and they'd say well I'm not - you can't come in if you're from the church. And a lot of church workers still have that idea that if a person has a tidy home - and nice furnit
ure they need no help and no Christmas parcels because they're clean and decent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So if they're scruffy and dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 They get it. I came up that a lot. And it is still true - it's a great pity because if a persons worked hard all their life and - a
 chair can be old and kept beautifully but they brought that chair when it was perhaps half-a-crown and they'd saved up for it then so of course it looks nice now because it's an antique - that doesn't mean to say they've got more money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So you do feel a little bit better about this section?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about teachers though - who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Mostly their own class but if they - they would pop in occasionally and see your parents. They'd take an interest I mean if you - if y
ou were getting on at school, enough interest to come and see your people, but I think mainly they kept together, visited each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Teachers would?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you know anything about farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Only on holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you know who they would move with socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
They moved with farmers on the same - more or less on the same footing as them - selves. Such a farmer down the road would visit a farmer up the road but he wouldn't expect the labourers to come anywhere near - they had the
ir own meeting on their own labouring sort of - they - they tended to be very much of a class see, the owner farmers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 More so than say the clergy or the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh they were very top-dog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Because they were wealthy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Not so much that - they were employers. And if you - you did as you were told - there was no going on strike then - you were just out. They had the final word. In fact in the building trade - this is going back sometime - 
they not only had the - the foreman had the final word, underneath builder there - and he would turn a man off the job directly the ceiling was done - he couldn't finish the week - the week. That was finished - they wanted to save money. And they'd be out
 of work with no money coming in during the slack period. No keeping them on - keeping them on like they do now - no dole. So they got very bad times. People on that type of work really did have a very hard time of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Your grandparents for example were employers weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Would you class them in the same category as these people you've just been talking about - were they top-dog?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no, because 3/8 I think there - you see grandfather had worked himself up from from the b
ottom and it was also in Hoxton - which is a rough and ready district but he was so very well liked - matter of fact he's not a Jew - or he wasn't a Jew - but they all thought he was and he footed a bill for somebody as a young man - let him down - he wen
t bankrupt. And all the Jews round Hoxton and Shoreditch gave him credit 'til he started again - so he must have been well liked whatever he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So you're really thinking of large scale employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Yes, individuals - I mean if - after all if
 an individual small firm like my grandfather - if he'd - sort of upset his employees he'd probably have had to go out of business 'cos he only had - perhaps four and they were there all their lives pretty well. That they tended more to sort have almost a
s much say in what they made as - as he did. He respected their knowledge - and they respected his ability.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But the other kind of employer would tend to associate with a similar sort of person as himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Definitely, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What sort of people would you say went to the church and what sort went to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Church people - those that liked - you mean Church of England? Those that liked to dress up on Sunday in their best, which I don't disagree with actually because after all if yo
u go to a party you dress in your best - therefore if you go to the house of God you should dress nicely too, but these people didn't do it for that reason, they did it to be better than Mrs Jones next door - she had a new hat last week, I'll have a new h
at this week - don't I sound dreadful. But .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Would this happen in the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, not so much.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you think people of a higher social class went to church than to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I do, yes, because it was the Church of England and the Vic
ar went there you know and - and chapel it was a Minister and of course there's not so much ritual about chapel - and I went - tell you something, I remembered this and it really is a memory from the time I was seven. We were living at Finsbury Park and a
 
lady there did a lot of good works - it was when we were in the flat - and one day she said, "Come along Doris I'm sure you'd like to come to our meeting, I'm taking it today." She had quite a deal of money and she used to give a lot and provide a lot - p
r
ovide the teas and this sort of thing. So along goes me in the back pew - nobody knew I was with her. And there were three old ladies in front and I heard one say to the other - "just butter her up dear and she'll give you anything you want." I've remembe
red that ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 This was when you were seven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Yes. And I've never forgotten that. Because that's the way they looked and Mrs Robinson was doing her best to give them a good afternoon and to help them. I've never really believed anybody that 
says anything nice since. I always I think they're putting it on you know. Help \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 my old ladies. That's the way they looked at anybody with a little bit of money who tried to help. But she wasn't a nasty stand-offish - she was a - friendly, elder
ly, quite a dumpy sort of woman that always dressed in an old fashioned style, you know, never set herself off in all these high faluting clothes or - always the same old black high necked dress. Horrible old cats - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Can you remember any of the places you lived where there were many Roman Catholics
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You didn't come across many at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
I have met Roman Catholics - I have the greatest admiration for the Roman Catholic religion. There were some in the same road at - Finchley. Our F
rench maid was a Roman Catholic and I visited several convents when I had French people and - my admiration stems for the fact that I think they have a - a useful sort of religion, in other words you give your first service to God first thing in the morni
ng then the day's your own. It's not wrong to read a book - it's not wrong to dance on Sunday, because ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were people generally tolerant though or was it just something personal to you? Were the protestants tolerant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 They're rather inclined t
o be bigoted. But to my mind I can't see that God is at all upset when he sees someone dancing happily. There's such ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Some people did feel this about the Roman Catholics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. I know people now haven't got a good word to say for them. Mind yo
u I don't agree with the Pope's ruling - so I wouldn't be a Roman Catholic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But were they looked down on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 They were - they still are you know - regarded as case.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were you aware of this when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I think always - onl
y of course as I say, I did come up against a lot of French people - I don't really know why but I did. And they used to - take me round to the various convents that quite a number of convents had boarded the French girls then - not as schools but busines
s girls. And I would ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 They lodged there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
That's it. I was so pleased with the way they went on there. It was to my mind very sensible. I have met one or two church meeting - there's one at Hampstead where they have the - golfers leave their g
olf clubs in the vestibule while they go into service before they play golf - which is completely sensible to my idea.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say that there were different
 groups within the lower classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
I would say different groups because you see you'd get somebody who perhaps knew how to cook and she would make the money go round. And then you could go down to the market and spend sevenpence at the Oden market and
 get enough meat to last you for a week. Well, if you didn't know that or couldn't cook it you'd have to either go without meat or do something - do something else you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You would again divide up the lower class in financial terms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How they spent their money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Would you divide it up in terms of skilled craftsmen and labourers or unemployed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Not necessarily because it wasn't really skilled craftsmen and - who took a delight in his work - it would take him so long 
to finish the job - say carpentry that his money would not from necessity be more than labourers for that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So you wouldn't divide them up in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. I mean some of those craftsmen have spent - months on carving a little article - they
'd get quite good money at the end but they got to live 'til they finished it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So you would divide it up in terms of how much money they had or how they spent it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And how they spent it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Can you think of any particular families who you would put into different groups or are you just thinking of them generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, I was just thinking generally because .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you come in contact much with the working classes as families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Not now - no. And as I say, when I was young you hid i
t if you worked because it wasn't considered quite the thing - if the woman of the house worked that would all be sort of done back, I mean, if she did a bit of sewing or a little bit of mending or anything like that it would never be known because it wou
ld - meant her husband wasn't capable of keeping her. You see that's a very much better idea now. Because - after all you get someone who's been a busy woman all her life she gets }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8737982 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047  she's got her home - no - no family - well, she'd get bored stiff now, I mean, the education is much higher - she's got to use her mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But people just didn't accept this idea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no, no, they didn't - it was not considered correct.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you think that one group of the working class felt itself superior to the others
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Which group would you think felt superior?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Well, you get - practically any group that was slightly above the other - I mean you'd get say the crossing sweeper - you know - because he just worked outside. You'd get the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7295018\charrsid5596047 people \endash 
 tai}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
loresses and people like that - they were fairly low because they had such low money and had to work all the time, but the tailor himself is coming higher - much higher - although he's working all day.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 He was a working class man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Yes. But the shop 3/8 now the shop assistant would be fairly low - specially the one that sweeps the floors and of course the errand boy was just beyond the pale. But they could all work up if they wanted to, but you see you tended to - hot to be able to
 do that - well, seamstresses never even had a chance to work up in a small businesses. There they were stitching away from .......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were some families thought of as rough in the working classes and other as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. And that mainly depe
nded on clothing. They looked rough and were dirty - a respectable class would wash their hands and face. The rough ones didn't bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Would labourers automatically be one of the rough ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Not automatically - no. If they - if they came home a
nd changed and had a bath - not a bath - a wash and you know put a decent coat on they wouldn't be considered - the bottom. But it was their off duty - they were sort of more socially up to the minute you might say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Father was more lenient I should say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you know why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You don't think it was because he was a man or because of his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I don't think so - I think it was just beca
use he had things easier than mother. I don't mean financially but he was the baby of the family and mother was the eldest of nine and I think her mother had eloped with grandfather when she was seventeen and - matter of fact she went back next day becaus
e she said she didn't like being }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8737982 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
. Her parents sent her back to her husband and said the only thing they said no was because she was so young. Well mother was born fairly soon but grandma wasn't nineteen then you see and she was very hard on mother. 
Mother quite - I don't know mother - she said you know when I went to business I had to hide my money, she thought she could spend it a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7295018\charrsid5596047 ll you know. But I think it stem}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 med from that, dad had always been made a fuss of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So his attitude to life was more easy going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was just that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And your mother saw herself as belonging to the - which class - the middle middle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Because of her marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Not easily. You could, but it would probably mean moving out of the district.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Can you remember anyone who did change classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I think I've heard that more since I'm older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Not at that time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Not at that time - no. You often hear it now. And not at that time - it was just taken for granted that they were or weren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes, they used to have their regular beats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh I thought they were wonderful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Where you ever threatened with the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no, you always told a policeman if you wanted anything. You w
ant to know the time ask a policeman was the - the saying in my day. No, I think they had a very good name at - that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How do you think he treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I just remembered - talking about going out of class - I had a cousin who went to Afri
ca - she was our class I should say - she went out as a tailoress with no job, when she got there she couldn't get a job so she served in a dairy. And - in the dairy she met this man who she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8737982 Married}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047  and she rose to entertain the - this present Queen Mother
 when she was Duchess of Walworth - and she visited - er - one of the coast stations out there and all her clothes - clothes and things she had a big establishment with P }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3822165 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047  O and that sort of thing so she obviously got out of her class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But this was only by moving away and marrying somebody in a good position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So it could be done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh it could be done. Mind you she must have had the intelligence to - she never pretended to be anything that she wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You wouldn't think this was typical though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I shouldn't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about people moving up from the working class into middle class - was there more chance of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 They - I think if they - they'd have to move away - I'm sure otherwise they - the friends o
n both sides would take it out of them. You know say oh you're putting it on aren't you? That style about it you know - think yourself someone - that style. But I should say if they moved away they could do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How do you think the policeman treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Oh well he was regarded with super respect and treated people respectfully and he just said move on and they moved on, they're not like they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And you think he treated people fairly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh definitely. I mean, you take a place lik
e Sevendales - which was a terrible place in my day - they went down in twos always they couldn't walk round that area unless there were two. But even then it was only come on clear out of here-no harsh treatment and that was a very bad area. They might u
se a truncheon but they didn't expect to be knifed or shot or anything like they are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Completely different really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was your home rented? Or did your parents buy the houses when they moved?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 When we had houses he bought them, when we lived in flats they - we rented them. Don't know why but that's how he .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 If you rented it did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Er - well, in both cases they lived in the same place as we did. Once we were in a house and the other on
e we were above a shop - where the shopkeeper ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh, we were great friends - oh they used to treat me as one of the family - I was always allowed to go anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So you never had any landlord problems?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I know they had to be very, very careful. Ends always did meet but - sometimes perhaps it was only just.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Is this when you were younger or when you were getting towards school leaving age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, I was always aware of the fact we had to be careful - right from my very first days. You - you mustn't fritter things away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Almost certainly you had enough to be comfortable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 We had - oh we had plenty to be comfortable but you had to be careful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I just grew up with it - I still do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did it worry you or make you angry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was your father ever ill or ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Dad was much mor
e delicate than mother when he was younger. But - he was never laid up - he just sort of had a day off and - whenever .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 He was never out of work for long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no, no, it was just - overtiredness they'd call it now I expect. But you didn't have all these nervous things then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So really he worked all his working life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 All his life - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You never had to depend on your savings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was there someone in the district that people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
No, I think on the whole that people were very - very tolerant in so far as - they just couldn't be bothered, I mean, you wouldn't get demonstrators unless it was something very, very special like people b
eing out of work for eight weeks or something like that. Normally they would just say oh not going there - don't like him and you - if you went into a political meeting it was more - more like being in church - you all just sat there whilst the speaker dr
oned away you know, that sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 People didn't get so excited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You don't remember feeling}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7295018\charrsid5596047  that any families were victimis}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 ed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were you given lessons by one of your parents or by tutor or governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 When you first started what time of the morning did you go.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 We went all day from nine 'til four and went home at lunch time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 At the age of five you went from nine 'til four?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes. And you worked all the time there were no play lessons, but it was delightful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How long did you have for your lunch break?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh we'd go - we'd have about an hour and a half to two hours. Vaguely I think mother fetched me about jus
t after twelve and I got back at two. There were about twenty of us - it was thoroughly enjoyable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Little dame school - she just taught us everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 This wasn't a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No - oh no, it was a little
 private dame school - just by the reservoir down in Green Lanes - Finsbury Park and she was really wonderful teacher - of course we learnt a lot by rot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7295018\charrsid5596047 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047  - I mean we we just used to sing our twice one are two - twice two are four - this sort of thing and then we used to know all the reigns of the Kings of England you know 1066 and this sort of business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 From the age of five on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Always - from the time I left there about seven I knew an awful lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 This day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was it for boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 It was a mixed one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. And then arithmetic she ground - always into and spelling - never allowed to spell anything wrongly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So you really had things pumped into you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Walked.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 It was near enough to walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Mother took me because you had two big roads to cross.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I suppose we'd take about twenty minutes. Because you had to come up Wo
odbury Grove and across that big main road Seven Sisters then across Green Lanes and down Green Lanes to the bottom their.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Quite a long walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You said you liked school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I loved school. Very happy at school. Liked home work - loved doing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How did you feel about the teacher - the dame?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh she was very pleasant - she taught me - I don't even remember her - I only remember being taught.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You can't remember what she was like - if she was strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, I - oh she must have been pretty strict because she kept us all - I never remember any of us being in trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 There were twenty-five of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did she emphasise certain things as important in life - manners or tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no, we were just expected to keep our books clean and if you did a blot you started all over again. Just sort of automatic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were you encouraged to speak in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No, I don't remember - it was mainly writing work I think she got on with. Yes. She certainly knew the ground work very, very well.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And it was a little private school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Yes. It was just in the front room of her house. I don't even remember we had a playtime - I suppose we did have a break but I know we weren't allowed in the garden or anything like that. We probably just stood and talked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 If you did something the teacher disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh, you'd probably have to do a few - if she - you were really bad - you'd do a few lines of handwriting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Would the girls have to do this in the same way as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Can you think of anything someone might do that the teachers would disapprove of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh only if they were consistently disobedient and wouldn't do their - writing properly and that sort 
of thing and of course we weren't allowed to throw rubbers at each other or anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So you remember it as a very well behaved little school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Very, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Always. Right through, yes. Great interest yes, oh yes great interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did they visit the school? Did mother meet the dame?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Er - well, little one - didn't have any speech days or anything -
 they did later on they always came to prize giving and that sort of thing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, we were all about the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did the dames single out any child for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No, she was very good as far as I remember none of us ever felt any different from any others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were there any little groups of you or cliques?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Not in that school. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, I was one of the - we were a very integrated whole.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What age did you leave there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Er - seven. Then I went to Palmers Green and I went to the Elementary - Haselwood Lane school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 This was a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. All day schools - never went to boarding schools. Oh you mean like the type of school - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was this a mixed one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How old were you when you left that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Nine. Well, for three years it was because you know it wasn't the exact
 age. I went you know sort of beginning of seven at the end of - yes nearly three .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you leave this school because you moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How did you get to that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 With your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, I went on my own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you have a mid-day meal there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, always went home mid-day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were the hours very much the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 About the same - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What did you think of this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh I enjoyed that too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You liked the teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. G
ot on very well - that was where I was a fairy queen and whatever it was - a Dutch girl - oh mother would make my costumes and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 This was the beginning of your drama activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 At this school did the teacher emphasise behaving in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no. There were a lot of children - we automatically behaved quite well
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 It wasn't instilled in you that you should be polite to people or you should be punctual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, you see, you - oh you had to be punctual e
lse you'd be in trouble and you always got up when the mistress came in the room and that sort of thing you see said good morning when they came in then you sat down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But you just knew this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, well you all did it - it was just reckoned to be done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What happened if anybody misbehaved at this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Very badly - oh you'd be sent off to the Head and be caned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Would girls be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes, girls were reckoned the same as boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What sort of offence would be classed as misbehaving very badly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Well, that might be say throwing the ink bottle at something or - ink well rather - something like that you see, making a mess, well, things...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What about minor offences?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh minor offences the mistress would deal with or the master.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Lines or some extra sums or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Would they smack you with a ruler or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 They could do if they wanted to but they very rarely did - they very rarely had to. See, there was a sense of discipline in
 those days. I mean they - they stand and blow the whistle when we were all in the playground rushing about like lunatics and everybody would line up automatically and - all at once. Another whistle and you'd all march off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Without having to be specifically told?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did the other children at this school come from similar sort of home to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Quite a lot - because all round was a newish estate then - they all came from that type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were there any groups in this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh, we tended there because the - the forms were all quite large. You tended there to - to be in groups of five or six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were there for example any work house children that you know of at this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Not that I know of - no. Those that I visited as I say were in - the little modern houses round about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So you weren't aware of any other type of child that would have been left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No. No. No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, well as I remember we played various games in the playground with perhaps the whole from played them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What sort of games did you play in the playground?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
I've forgotten the name of it now - you have somebody and you take prisoners into gaol, you smack their hands when they're running about then take take them off to gaol a
nd there's a gaol - goal keeper there and he holds them in while somebody - another pal trie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7295018\charrsid5596047 s and comes along, sneaks around}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
 and pats their hand and then they can come out - I remember that one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So you always did tend to play these games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes, we always played - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What school did you go to after that one? Another Elementary one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, I went to Clarkes College after that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 That was at Sydenham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What sort of school was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, it was an 
offshoot of the Clarkes College at Catford. This - the one that I went to was in a big house run by one mistress - a German - oh and she was clever and she could teach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was that a private school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, it's mainly - as you know it's still going 
- Clarkes College - that they ran this sort of - I suppose you'd call it primary department at Forest Hill, she ran it. It closed down when she - when the first world war started 'cos she was German you see. But she - and she there - we were what - all ab
out the same age-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 About nine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Nine to eleven you see up there. Well she took - there was three of us - myself and two boys - and she worked us up for our exams. After hours anytime she'd do it - we took - Oxford Prelim and Oxford Junior, Polyceps
 Junior and there - of course I didn't reckon to but just the three of us we - we could do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How many were there in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Round about twenty there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And she took you all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 She took the whole lot. And she gave us special tuition to - for exams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you have to pay fees at this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Oh yes. And father.....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 It was a private?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, it was pri - Clarkes College too you know - pay just the same - and of course since we were taking these exams all the fees
 and extra books your parents paid for because ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What was Clarkes College?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well it mainly teaches commercial courses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 It always did. Why this branch was stuck with - preliminary I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And this was 'til the age of eleven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And again you liked this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes, yes. Thoroughly enjoyed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you play in there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes, we had - we played in the garden and - ball games and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And again were all the children there from a similar sort of background to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Definitely there. See that was all paying - they had to pay - wasn't ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What happened when you left there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well - now I left - I left there later on - but we were the
re - I must have been - where did we go after - to Finchley from there so I must - I was about thirteen when finally left there 'cos I'd taken all my exams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You stayed on until you were thirteen at Clarkes College?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Yes. And I got to - North
 Finchley - Middlesex - was a secondary school - I think it still is - in the main road. At fourteen I went straight into the middle school - that was a big council school - we paid then. You were paying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 This was a council school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Council school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 That the same as a board?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Secondary school. And - I stopped there until I left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So when you moved to Finchley you then went to this secondary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You went on your own - did you cycle to that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, I cycled.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And were the hours the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Roughly the same - and I usually had lunch there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 At school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. They were a proper lunch - you see we had cookery classes there and the cookery class cooked the lunch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What did you have for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh be good lunches. Have meat and two vegetables and pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What size was this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I should say roughly - between four and five hundred.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 The cookery class didn't cook for -?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh well, you can cook - they'd 
cook - have all sorts of classes you see - a huge - huge room up there. And all the girls made - one lot put salt instead of sugar in blancmanges one time I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Quite an undertaking for the cookery class to cook for the whole school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you like that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes. Took me some time to get used to it 'cos they didn't work hard enough to my mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And you'd been used to small schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I'd been used to small school working hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was the discipline and respect the same as the other schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Just the same yes, oh yes. More so in fact I think - the headmaster - we had a headmistress for the girls side - headmaster over the headmistress too but they were greatly respected - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And you knew what was expected of you in terms of manners and punctuality and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What did you think about this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 After I got used to the fact that they didn't want you to do five hours homework - in fact they'd get annoyed if you did - I thoroug
hly enjoyed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were the children from similar sort of backgrounds to yourself or was it more varied at this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 They were a bit more varied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What groups did you tend to associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, my greatest friends mother kept a shop
. She was very good. But the other two - don't know what their parents were but they didn't keep shops - they lived in ordinary houses so I suppose their fathers went out to business or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Were you aware of any children who were treated differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No, - we - you see we all wore school uniform - you wouldn't know the difference at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You weren't aware of the background - any workhouse children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no, no. You see you got a definite school uniform you can be anybody. White blouses and gym tunics. And everybody had to wear them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And again your parents participated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh always came to anything - a speechdays and sports days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was this your last school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How old were you when you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Seventeen and a half. I was engaged.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Was it usual to stay as long as this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Well, I stayed on - two of us stayed on and worked as the headmaster's secretary to get up my typewriting and shorthand. It wasn't paid job but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What age did you finish formal education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Sixteen. Well I took - that was fifteen when I took metric - so I was sixteen just at the end of that term. Then I went on with .....

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 For a year and a half you acted as the headmaster's secretary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Could you have stayed on longer than sixteen at that school and be receiving education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 
Not unless - not unless you'd - you were going on to the university - then they would have kept you til you were the right age. You see, at that time there were several 
of us my age we took metric but you weren't allowed to hold the certificate until you were sixteen - we were fifteen - by the time we got the certificate we were sixteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you continue to wear school uniform when you were working as the headmaster's secretary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes, yes, yes. Well it was unpaid - it was really to get - give us - shorthand-typewriting and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you write his school letters and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Mainly we wrote manuscripts - I don't know where he got them - manuscripts - people used to send him manuscripts and we used to type them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But in a way you were still a school girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 But you weren't doing the normal sort of school studies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, that's right, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you attend any evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 At that time or ever after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Do you have any regrets about your education at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You were quite content?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Well, you see, the school wanted me to go on to the university but I got engaged so I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Is that the only reason why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Mm. When I got engaged I went to business, I mean there was no point in going to university and getting a degree if I was going to get }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8737982 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047  - you didn't work after marriage in those days you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did your parents mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Mother was very upset because she wanted me to be a teacher. Dad didn't mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And you said the headmistress would have liked you to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Seventeen and half years engaged.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I was engaged for three and a half years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 While you were at school did you have a part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I only had the one. I went to Brown Bavary - swiss engineers - yes - swiss engineers. And they were in l
ower Regent Street - Piccadilly. Then. They've moved now - they're near the Army and Navy stores.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 How do you spell Bavary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Boveri - that's swiss. Big engineering works - turbo-generators - they did the Battersea Power station all that lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Tubo-generators?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 This is when you were seventeen and a half?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 What were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 I was type - shorthand typist to the - what did they call him - the manage - the manager there - then after - after I think a year th
ey wanted me to-become assistant to the secretary which I was but didn't like so much because that was a silly woman. Then I left when I - to get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8737982 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047  at twenty-one. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 So when you started at Brown Boveri you were in - this was in 1920 - this was after the war wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 1920?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And that was the only job you ever had although you changed your position in the firm?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. I was quite happy in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You didn't want to be a teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 The training period for being a secretary was undertaken at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You learned your shorthand and typing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes, I took my exams from school too you see, the shorthand exams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you belong to any professional organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, we were definitely apart. Typists pool was a typists pool and nothing to do with the - with the management.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Nowadays some people say that there's a very big difference between craftsmen and other workers - between trained or skilled craftsmen.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 And other workers - did you feel that at the time you were working or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, I think we tended more or less - us typists tended not to take much interest in the firm as a firm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You were rather separate from the rest of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you continue to live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Oh, not really. I gave mother something out of my money. I think that's about the only - only thing - only difference it made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 You'd always had a fairly easy relationship with them any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Yes. Yes. And I mean she could go out in the day and didn't have to be there perhaps if I got home or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Well, of course when I - I was engaged by this time so we might go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you go to church then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No, I didn't go to church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6519033 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14834826 DT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1072918\charrsid5596047 No - never been interested in politics.
